oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: J. R. Hull & Alvin C. York
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Sgt. Alvin C. York is shown laughing at some remark made by J. R. Hull (uncle of Cordell Hull) at the draft office in Jamestown, Fentress County. Sergeant York is in a business suit and Mr. Hull is shown in a denim jacket and wearing a leather mitten.
Alvin Cullum York is a Congressional Medal of Honor winner and hero of World War I, was born in Pall Mall, Fentress County, Tennessee.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
